const BLACKLISTED_SUBSTRINGS = [' - ', '  ', 'lastfm'];

const MIN_TAG_NAME_LENGTH = 2;
const MAX_TAG_NAME_LENGTH = 40;
const TAG_RE = /^\w[\w -]*[a-z][\w -]*\w$/;

function isTagBlacklisted(tagName) {
  let result = false;

  if (tagName.length < MIN_TAG_NAME_LENGTH) {
    result = true;
  } else if (tagName.length > MAX_TAG_NAME_LENGTH) {
    result = true;
  } else if (!TAG_RE.test(tagName)) {
    return true;  
  } else if (BLACKLISTED_TAGS.has(tagName)) {
    result = true;
  } else if (
    BLACKLISTED_TAG_STARTS.some((blacklistedTagStart) =>
      tagName.startsWith(blacklistedTagStart),
    )
  ) {
    result = true;
  } else if (
    BLACKLISTED_TAG_ENDS.some(blacklistedTagEnd =>
      tagName.endsWith(blacklistedTagEnd),
    )
  ) {
    result = true;
  } else if (
    BLACKLISTED_SUBSTRINGS.some((blacklistedSubstring) =>
      tagName.includes(blacklistedSubstring),
    )
  ) {
    result = true;
  }

  return result;
}

return $input.all().map(item=> 
  ({
    ...item,
    json: {
      ...item.json,
      tags: item.json.tags.filter(tag => 
        !isTagBlacklisted(tag.name.toLowerCase()))
    }
  })
);

parameters.query:
DELETE FROM public."AlbumTag"
WHERE "albumArtist" = '{{ $json.artistName.replaceAll('\'', '\'\'') }}'
AND "albumName" = '{{ $json.name.replaceAll('\'', '\'\'') }}'
AND "tagName" NOT IN ({{ $json.tags.length ? $json.tags.map(tag => '\'' + tag.name + '\'').join(',') : `''` }});
